This paper proposes a method for generating trajectories using inverse reinforcement learning and activity forecasting. The use of convolutional value iteration suggests a focus on reinforcement learning and sequential decision-making, which is often associated with the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The use of 2D and 3D activity forecasting suggests a focus on computer vision and image processing, which is often associated with the cs.CV sub-category. The use of seabird trajectories suggests a focus on robotics and autonomous systems, which is often associated with the cs.RO and cs.SY sub-categories.
